<HEADLINE>
FT  15 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Administrator considers sale of Macmillan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Price Waterhouse, administrators to the Maxwell Communication Corporation
plans to push ahead with investigating the possibility of a private sale of
Macmillan, the US publisher, writes Raymond Snoddy.
Last year Price Waterhouse said it planned to sell the non-publishing
interests of MCC including the Official Airline Guides. The process of
selling OAG is now into the second round. Those interested include Reed
Elsevier, the international publishing group.
Although a sale of Macmillan was never ruled out Price Waterhouse had
previously suggested that a flotation towards the end of next year was more
likely.
Mr Mark Homan, senior joint administrator said yesterday it had always been
intended to consider a sale of Macmillan 'within the framework of a
potential public offering'.
'In recent weeks both we and our US advisers JP Morgan have been inundated
with expressions of interest in Macmillan and in Official Airline Guides,'
Mr Homan said.
</TEXT>
