<BYLINE>
   By ANTONY THORNCROFT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Top price at an auction of the contents of Robert Maxwell's home in Oxford
was the Pounds 60,900 paid for a view of Jerusalem (above) by the Israeli
artist Reuven Rubin, Antony Thorncroft writes.
Possessions from Headington Hill Hall including reproduction Georgian
furniture and video recorders went under the hammer at Sotheby's in London.
