FT  15 JAN 93 / World Trade News: US trade officials hold out little hope of
early end to Uruguay Round
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCES WILLIAMS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
US TRADE officials in Geneva yesterday held out little prospect of an early
conclusion to the Uruguay Round but said negotiations would continue in the
hope of progress by next Tuesday's stock-taking meeting of the top-level
Trade Negotiations Committee, writes Frances Williams.
Trade negotiators will try to present the Clinton administration, which
takes office the following day, with as few outstanding problems as
possible, in the dwindling hope that an accord can still be reached before
the current US negotiators' authority expires on March 2.
A senior US negotiator said a number of 'significant sticking points'
remained in talks with the EC on industrial tariffs, and there had been
little progress in resolving vital issues in separate discussions on the
draft package of Uruguay Round rules. There were also still differences with
the EC over agriculture.
</TEXT>
