</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ISRAELI troops shot dead three Palestinians and wounded 55 in three separate
incidents in the occupied territories yesterday, Palestinians said, Reuter
reports from Jerusalem.
The toll brings to 990 the number of Arabs killed by Israeli soldiers and
civilians in a five-year-old Palestinian uprising against Israeli rule in
the West Bank and Gaza Strip.
Yesterday's incidents took place in Dir el Balach and nearby Khan Yunis in
the occupied Gaza Strip and in the village of Jenin on the West Bank.
Israeli MP Mr Benjamin Netanyahu has suffered a setback in his campaign to
become the next leader of the opposition Likud party.
A media superstar during the Gulf war, Mr Netanyahu admitted yesterday to
having an extra-marital affair and said he was being blackmailed by a member
of his own party.
He was in the midst of a heated primary campaign for leadership of the
opposition Likud party which many believed he would win.
