FT  15 JAN 93 / World News in Brief: Honecker's haven
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Former East German leader Erich Honecker flew in to Santiago, Chile, to be
reunited with his family. The 80-year-old, who is suffering from liver
cancer, showed his bag of medicines on his flight from Germany, where his
manslaughter trial in was abandoned when the court learned his condition was
terminal.
