<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 93 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MEXICAN stocks lost ground on nervousness picked up from foreign markets
following the US and allied military attack on Iraq, but saw some recovery
by the close. The BMV index of 40 active stocks lost 18.3 at 1,763.8, after
falling to 1,732.6. Telmex shed 0.57 per cent on conservative assumptions
about its performance in the fourth quarter of 1992.
