<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
WOOL Australian wool prices drifted gradually lower at the opening sales of
the second half of the selling season this week. The AWC market indicator
was 500 cents a kg on January 13, down 9 cents. Farmers are putting up some
resistance to what for the vast majority are uneconomic prices and
withdrawing wool at their own reserves or prior to the sale, but this in the
longer term only means that more re-offered wool may later come onto the
market. Christmas Sales were very low with almost 4 million bales
overhanging the market. Excess of supply keeps buying slow and cautious.
</TEXT>
