<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 93 / International Capital Markets: Warburg unit to deal in China
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN BROWN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
POTTER Warburg Securities, the Australian stockbroking firm, has been
awarded a licence to deal on the Shenzhen stock exchange, the larger of
China's two fledgling stock markets.
Potter Warburg, a subsidiary of S. G. Warburg of the UK, is the first
Australian broker to be awarded a licence since foreign firms were invited
to apply in September by the People's Bank of China.
The licence will allow the firm to underwrite and distribute Chinese issues
to foreign investors. Foreign brokers licensed to operate at Shenzhen
include Credit Lyonnais, Yamaichi International and Swiss Bank Finance Asia.
