<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 93 / International Company News in Brief: Credit Lyonnais buys
Chase unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT, AP-DJ and REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK, PARIS, SINGAPORE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CREDIT Lyonnais yesterday said it had reached an agreement in principle to
acquire Chase Manhattan Bank Austria, the Austrian unit of Chase Manhattan
Bank, AP-DJ reports from Paris. Terms were not disclosed.
The French state-owned bank said that the acquisition, which must be
approved by Austrian banking authorities, would strengthen its presence in
Austria. Until now, Credit Lyonnais has had a representative office in the
country. Credit Lyonnais said Chase wwould retain a representative office in
Vienna.
Chase Austria is capitalised at Sch20m (Dollars 1.75m) and had assets almost
Sch2.5bn at the end of 1991.
The Chase unit specialises in lending and services to corporations and
selected private customers. The French bank said the acquisitions fits in
with its recent acquisition of BfG Bank of Germany.
*****
SEARS, Roebuck, the large US retail and financial services group, is selling
its business centres division to InaCom, a Nebraska-based company which
markets computer systems and services, for an undisclosed sum, writes Nikki
Tait in New York.
*****
COLD Storage, a Singapore-listed subsidiary of Australian food group Goodman
Fielder, is to buy a 70 per cent stake in Standard Confectionery, a
Malaysian fresh and frozen cakemaker, for about MDollars 15m (USDollars
5.8m), Reuter reports from Singapore.
The investment was 'part of Goodman Fielder's strategy to transform Cold
Storage into a leading regional consumer-food manufacturing and distributing
company,' CSH said.
