FT  14 JAN 93 / UK Company News: Mayflower Dollars 7.5m US buy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GRIFFITHS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MAYFLOWER Corporation, the specialist motor engineering group, is to expand
its US operations through the purchase of an Ohio stamping facility for
Dollars 7.5m (Pounds 4.9m) cash.
It will use the facilities to produce steel and aluminium panels for truck
and niche car markets.
Mayflower already owns Motor Panels, the Coventry-headquartered concern
which claims to be the world's largest independent designer of truck cabs
and car and truck bodies.
Motor Panels supplies bodies for Jaguar, Rolls-Royce and Rover among others,
as well as truck cabs for Leyland DAF and Iveco Ford. Its Ohio and North
Caroliner-based subsidiary supplies cabs for Mack, Freightliner, Western
Star and Autocar trucks.
Mayflower said yesterday that its latest acquisition, the assets of
Shadyside Stamping Plant, of Shadyside, Ohio, would broaden its supply
capability to the US motor industry.
