<HEADLINE>
FT  14 JAN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Tories reduce Labour poll lead
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LABOUR'S opinion-poll lead has been cut to 4 per cent in a survey for
today's Guardian.
The ICM survey shows the Conservatives as being considered to have the best
economic policies - recapturing the advantage they lost as a result of Black
Wednesday.
Voting intention figures put the Tories at 38 per cent, up 5 per cent since
December; Labour 42 per cent, down 3 per cent; Liberal Democrats 15 per
cent, down 1 per cent and others 5 per cent, down 1 per cent.
Just 24 per cent of interviewees said the Conservatives had the best
policies for the economy, but this was up 5 per cent from December and
enough to put them 1 per cent in front of Labour on the issue.
</TEXT>
