FT  14 JAN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Mental health review announced
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AN urgent review is to be conducted into whether new legal powers are needed
to ensure that the mentally ill get proper care in the community, Mrs
Virginia Bottomley, health secretary, said last night.
In a Commons written reply, Mrs Bottomley said that the Royal College of
Psychiatrists had recommended the 1983 Mental Health Act should be amended
to provide for a community supervision order. That would apply for patients
repeatedly admitted to hospital who needed long-term support in the
community but had a history of failing to co-operate with treatment.
'We do need to address, as a priority, whether we are doing enough to ensure
that these vulnerable people keep in contact with the services available,'
Mrs Bottomley said.
