FT  14 JAN 93 / George Walker's Pall Mall home up for sale
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr George Walker's former Pall Mall penthouse home, is up for sale with a
price tag of Pounds 1.45m, Maggie Urry writes.
Mr Walker, once chairman and chief executive of Brent Walker, the property
and leisure group, was last week arrested on charges of theft and false
account-ing.
He and his wife Jean had already vacated the flat, on the fifth and sixth
floor of the Palladian-style building, which overlooks St James's.
The flat has four reception rooms, including a 'rather grand drawing room'
according to Mellersh &amp; Harding, the agents, also four bedrooms and three
bathrooms.
Reports that Mr and Mrs Walker removed the kitchen they had installed,
before departing, are borne out by the agent's particulars which say the
kitchen 'requires complete renovation'.
