FT  14 JAN 93 / Ford executive new Acas chairman
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR John Hougham, the 55-year-old head of employee relations at Ford UK, is
to become chairman of Acas, the government conciliation service, David
Goodhart writes.
Mr Hougham beat a strong field, including Ms Brenda Dean, the former print
union leader, and Mr Mike Bett, deputy chairman of BT. His appointment is
expected to be formally announced by the Department of Employment today.
Mr Hougham is a respected negotiator who has been at Ford since 1963. One
senior trade unionist said yesterday: 'He has a reputation as a bit of a
tough guy and he has certainly been in some big fights at Ford, but he is
well respected on both sides of industry.'
