FT  14 JAN 93 / Embarrassment for President-elect Clinton
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Next week's inaugural celebrations lost a party yesterday and left
President-elect Bill Clinton somewhat embarrassed. A planned Sunday gala
honouring Mr Ron Brown, commerce secretary-designate, and Democrat party
chairman for four years, was cancelled over controversy about corporate
funding for the event.
He has come under attack for his Washington lobbying business, including
representing foreign companies, and for the severance terms he has arranged
from his law firm.
This probably does not threaten his nomination, but news of the gala, with a
US subsidiary of Sony of Japan covering some costs, appeared to compound
suspicions of conflicts of interest.
